Package tree.node

Interface ITreeNode<NODETYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    NODETYPE - determines the type of the ITreeNode. This type is replaced with the concrete type during instantiation. It has to match the type of the ITree in which the ITreeNode is used.
    All Superinterfaces:
    IDeepCopy, ISearchableByFilter<ITreeNode<NODETYPE>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CategoryTreeNode, CopyableTreeNode, GenericTreeNode, ProductCategoryTreeNode, ProductTreeNode
    public interface ITreeNode<NODETYPE>
extends IDeepCopy, ISearchableByFilter<ITreeNode<NODETYPE>>
    This interface specifies the behavior of a node in an ITree. It allows retrieving its value and label and, in addition, to check whether the node is a leaf or not (e.g. it has child ITreeNode). Furthermore, it specifies methods to find ITreeNodes and generate a meaningful output for a console application.

    The interface extends the IDeepCopy interface and thus copies of ITreeNodes can be created.

    The interface extends the ISearchableByFilter interface. This allows to filter ITreeNodes by an ISearchFilter. The result is returned as a Collection.

    Author:
    OOP

      • findNodeByValue

        ITreeNode<NODETYPE> findNodeByValue​(NODETYPE searchValue)
        This method searches the passed value in the ITreeNode and its sub-tree (all its children recursively). If a matching ITreeNode is found, it is returned (first hit). Otherwise NULL is returned.

        The comparison between the passed value and the ITreeNode is based on the method checkNodeByValue(Object).

        Parameters:
        searchValue - The value used to identify the searched ITreeNode.
        Returns:
        the ITreeNode if found, or NULL otherwise.

      • findNodeByNode

        ITreeNode<NODETYPE> findNodeByNode​(ITreeNode<NODETYPE> searchNode)
        This method searches the passed ITreeNode in the current ITreeNode and its sub-tree (all its children recursively). If a matching ITreeNode is found, it is returned (first hit). Otherwise NULL is returned.

        The comparison between the passed ITreeNode and the ITreeNode is based on the Object.equals(Object) method.

        Parameters:
        searchNode - The node used to identify the searched ITreeNode.
        Returns:
        the ITreeNode if found, or NULL otherwise.

      • removeNodeByValue

        boolean removeNodeByValue​(NODETYPE removeValue)
        This method removes an ITreeNode and all its children from the sub-tree. The passed value is used to identify the ITreeNode to be removed. If a matching ITreeNode is found, it is removed (first hit). In this case TRUE is returned. If no ITreeNode has been removed after the sub-tree has been processed, FALSE is returned.

        The comparison between the passed value and the ITreeNode is based on the method checkNodeByValue(Object).

        Parameters:
        removeValue - The value of the ITreeNode to be removed from the sub-tree.
        Returns:
        TRUE if an ITreeNode was removed, FALSE otherwise.

      • removeNodeByNode

        This method removes an ITreeNode and all its children from the sub-tree. The passed ITreeNode is used to identify the ITreeNode to be removed. If a matching ITreeNode is found, it is removed (first hit). In this case TRUE is returned. If no ITreeNode has been removed after the sub-tree has been processed, FALSE is returned.

        The comparison between the passed ITreeNode and the ITreeNode is based on the Object.equals(Object) method.

        Parameters:
        removeNode - The node used to identify the searched ITreeNode.
        Returns:
        the ITreeNode if found, or NULL otherwise.

      • checkNodeByValue

        boolean checkNodeByValue​(NODETYPE value)
        This method checks the ITreeNode against a passed value. If the passed value matches the ITreeNode then TRUE is returned. Otherwise FALSE is returned. A ITreeNode matches if the value of it is equals to the value to be checked against.
        Parameters:
        value - The value that the ITreeNode is checked against.
        Returns:
        TRUE if the passed value matches the ITreeNode, FALSE otherwise

      • generateConsoleView

        String generateConsoleView​(String spacer,
                           String preamble)
        Generates a String representation of the ITreeNode. The String representation contains the ITreeNode and its sub-tree (all its children recursively). Each direct child ITreeNode is placed in a separate line with a leading preamble. A spacer and a preamble are passed along to the method.
        Parameters:
        spacer - The String that should be used to separate ITreeNodes in the output.
        preamble - specifies the leading characters for the ITreeNode
        Returns:
        the generated String output of the ITreeNode

      • deepCopy

        ITreeNode<NODETYPE> deepCopy()
        Redefined here to limit the return type of the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method to ITreeNode.

        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 

         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements. While it is typically the case that: 
         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.
